{"lemma":"عِمْلاقَيْ","slug":"عِمْلاقَيْ","root":"ع.م.ل.ق","root_slug":"ع-م-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-م-ل-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30594"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%85%D9%92%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"huge, giant, gigantic, mammoth"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"super, super- (in compounds)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"great"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"giant","examples":[{"text":"اَلْعَمَالِقَة (al-ʕamāliqa)— the Amalekites (compare Hebrew עֲמָלֵק)"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕim.laːq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30594","headword_ar":"عِمْلَاقٌ","root":"Emlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who deceives"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTarofihi","text_ar":"بِطَرْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); (O, K, TA; in the TK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bZrfh","text_ar":"بظرفه"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biZarofihi","text_ar":"بِظَرْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his excel-lence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elegance, of mind, manners, and address"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bZurofih","text_ar":"بظُرْفِه"},{"kind":"text","text":";) so expl. by Ibn-'Abbád: (O:) or, accord. to the Nh, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who deceives men, and beguiles them with his speech."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamaAliyqu","text_ar":"عَمَالِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamaAliqapN","text_ar":"عَمَالِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamaAliqu","text_ar":"عَمَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is extr. (TA.)       -A2-  [And the pls.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamaAliyqu","text_ar":"العَمَالِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamaAliqapu","text_ar":"العَمَالِقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[are appellations applied by the Arabs to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Amalekites;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people of the descendants of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eimoliyq","text_ar":"عِمْلِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimolaAq","text_ar":"عِمْلَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Amalek"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K;) who was"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the son of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAwa*","text_ar":"لَاوَذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lud"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the son of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iram","text_ar":"اـِرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aram"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the son of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAm","text_ar":"سَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shem"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the son of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuwH","text_ar":"نُوح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Noah"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O, K;) or [rather,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who was the son of Lud, the son of Shem,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for,] accord. to the Mukaddameh Fádileeyeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAwa*","text_ar":"لَاوَذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was the brother of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iram","text_ar":"اـِرَم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they dispersed themselves in the countries,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and most of them became extinct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to IAth, they were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the remnant of the people of 'Ád"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAd","text_ar":"عَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"): Suh says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of them were the kings of Egypt, the Pharaohs, of whom were El-Weleed the son of Mus'ab, the consociate of Moses, and Er-Reiyán the son of El-Weleed, the consociate of Joseph."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","S","TA"]}]}}